<model name="Screening">
<purpose>Schedule when and where movies are shown</purpose>
<fields>
- movie: ObjectId, ref: 'Movie', required
- hall: ObjectId, ref: 'Hall', required
- startTime: Date, required (includes date and time)
- endTime: Date, required (auto-calculated: startTime + movie.durationMinutes)
- date: Date, required (extracted from startTime for query optimization)
- createdAt: Date
</fields>
<constraints>
- endTime MUST be auto-calculated on save
- startTime must be in the future (at creation time)
- date field must match startTime date
</constraints>
<business_rules>
<!-- This is the MOST CRITICAL business rule in the entire system -->

<critical_rule id="screening_overlap_prevention">
<description>
Two screenings in the SAME hall MUST NOT overlap in time on the SAME date.
</description>

<mathematical_definition>
Given:
- Existing screening: [existingStart, existingEnd]
- New screening: [newStart, newEnd]
- Same hall: existingHall === newHall

Overlap occurs IF:
  (existingStart < newEnd) AND (existingEnd > newStart)

Therefore, REJECT new screening IF:
  - Same hall
  - Same date
  - Time ranges overlap (using formula above)
</mathematical_definition>

<implementation_algorithm>
```javascript
// services/screeningService.js

static async _checkForOverlap(hallId, startTime, endTime, excludeScreeningId = null) {
  // Extract date for same-day comparison
  const screeningDate = new Date(startTime);
  screeningDate.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);
  
  const nextDay = new Date(screeningDate);
  nextDay.setDate(nextDay.getDate() + 1);
  
  // Find all screenings in same hall on same day
  const query = {
    hall: hallId,
    date: {
      $gte: screeningDate,
      $lt: nextDay
    }
  };
  
  // Exclude current screening if updating
  if (excludeScreeningId) {
    query._id = { $ne: excludeScreeningId };
  }
  
  const existingScreenings = await Screening.find(query);
  
  // Check for overlap with each existing screening
  for (const existing of existingScreenings) {
    const existingStart = existing.startTime;
    const existingEnd = existing.endTime;
    
    // Overlap detection formula
    const hasOverlap = (existingStart < endTime) && (existingEnd > startTime);
    
    if (hasOverlap) {
      throw new AppError(
        `Screening overlaps with existing screening from ${existingStart.toLocaleTimeString()} to ${existingEnd.toLocaleTimeString()}`,
        400
      );
    }
  }
  
  return true; // No overlap found
}
```
</implementation_algorithm>

